members.name: byteOrder
members.comment: The byte order of the stream as an instance of the enumeration class java.nio.ByteOrder, where ByteOrder.BIG_ENDIAN indicates network byte order and ByteOrder.LITTLE_ENDIAN indicates the reverse order. By default, the value is ByteOrder.BIG_ENDIAN.

members.name: streamPos
members.comment: The current read position within the stream. Subclasses are responsible for keeping this value current from any method they override that alters the read position.

members.name: bitOffset
members.comment: The current bit offset within the stream. Subclasses are responsible for keeping this value current from any method they override that alters the bit offset.

members.name: flushedPos
members.comment: The position prior to which data may be discarded. Seeking to a smaller position is not allowed. flushedPos will always be >= 0.

members.name: checkClosed
members.comment: Throws an IOException if the stream has been closed. Subclasses may call this method from any of their methods that require the stream not to be closed.

throws: IOException - if the stream is closed.

param: byteOrder - one of ByteOrder.BIG_ENDIAN or java.nio.ByteOrder.LITTLE_ENDIAN, indicating whether network byte order or its reverse will be used for future reads.

return: one of ByteOrder.BIG_ENDIAN or ByteOrder.LITTLE_ENDIAN, indicating which byte order is being used.

members.name: read
members.comment: Reads a single byte from the stream and returns it as an int between 0 and 255. If EOF is reached, -1 is returned. Subclasses must provide an implementation for this method. The subclass implementation should update the stream position before exiting. The bit offset within the stream must be reset to zero before the read occurs.

throws: IOException - if the stream has been closed.
return: the value of the next byte in the stream, or -1 if EOF is reached.

members.name: read
members.comment: A convenience method that calls read(b, 0, b.length). The bit offset within the stream is reset to zero before the read occurs.

param: b - an array of bytes to be written to.
throws: NullPointerException - if b is null.
IOException - if an I/O error occurs.
return: the number of bytes actually read, or -1 to indicate EOF.

members.name: read
members.comment: Reads up to len bytes from the stream, and stores them into b starting at index off. If no bytes can be read because the end of the stream has been reached, -1 is returned. The bit offset within the stream must be reset to zero before the read occurs. Subclasses must provide an implementation for this method. The subclass implementation should update the stream position before exiting.

param: b - an array of bytes to be written to.
off - the starting position within b to write to.
len - the maximum number of bytes to read.
throws: IndexOutOfBoundsException - if off is negative, len is negative, or off + len is greater than b.length.
NullPointerException - if b is null.
IOException - if an I/O error occurs.
return: the number of bytes actually read, or -1 to indicate EOF.

members.name: length
members.comment: Returns -1L to indicate that the stream has unknown length. Subclasses must override this method to provide actual length information.

return: -1L to indicate unknown length.

members.name: skipBytes
members.comment: Advances the current stream position by calling seek(getStreamPosition() + n). The bit offset is reset to zero.

param: n - the number of bytes to seek forward.
throws: IOException - if getStreamPosition throws an IOException when computing either the starting or ending position.
return: an int representing the number of bytes skipped.

members.name: mark
members.comment: Pushes the current stream position onto a stack of marked positions.

members.name: reset
members.comment: Resets the current stream byte and bit positions from the stack of marked positions. An IOException will be thrown if the previous marked position lies in the discarded portion of the stream.

throws: IOException - if an I/O error occurs.

param: pos - a long containing the length of the stream prefix that may be flushed.
throws: IOException - if an I/O error occurs.
IOException - if an I/O error occurs.

return: the earliest legal position for seeking, as a long.

members.name: isCached
members.comment: Default implementation returns false. Subclasses should override this if they cache data.

return: true if this ImageInputStream caches data.

members.name: isCachedMemory
members.comment: Default implementation returns false. Subclasses should override this if they cache data in main memory.

return: true if this ImageInputStream caches data in main memory.

members.name: isCachedFile
members.comment: Default implementation returns false. Subclasses should override this if they cache data in a temporary file.

return: true if this ImageInputStream caches data in a temporary file.

throws: IOException - if an I/O error occurs.

members.name: finalize
members.comment: Finalizes this object prior to garbage collection. The close method is called to close any open input source. This method should not be called from application code.

throws: Throwable - if an error occurs during superclass finalization.
